lead_paragraph: An article on Thursday about the scientific debate over a past examination of the cyclist Lance Armstrong’s muscle efficiency misidentified the publication that presented both the original research and new information about an error in the study. It is the Journal of Applied Physiology, not the Journal of Physiology.
